.TH KILL(1),User Commands,KILL(1)

.SH NAME
kill - terminate a process

.SH SYNOPSIS
kill pid

.SH DESCRIPTION
kill terminates the process whose bank number (process ID) is pid.

pid is parsed as a number in decimal, or in hexadecimal with a leading $ or 0x.

Only a single pid is accepted.
No signal selection is supported; the target process is killed unconditionally.

.SH DIAGNOSTICS
kill: ARG: argument must be process ID / bank - the pid could not be parsed as a number.

kill: (ARG) - No such process - no process currently occupies the given bank.

.SH EXIT STATUS
kill exits 0 whether or not the target process existed.

.SH SEE ALSO
ps(1)
